import React from 'react'; import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom'; const NewsScreen = () => { const navigate = useNavigate(); const newsItems = [ { id: 1, title: 'Tech Stocks Rally on AI Breakthrough', summary: 'Major technology companies see significant gains following new AI developments.', source: 'Financial Times', time: '2 hours ago', category: 'Technology' }, { id: 2, title: 'Federal Reserve Signals Rate Cut', summary: 'Central bank hints at potential interest rate reduction in next quarter.', source: 'Wall Street Journal', time: '4 hours ago', category: 'Economy' }, { id: 3, title: 'Tesla Reports Record Q4 Earnings', summary: 'Electric vehicle manufacturer exceeds analyst expectations with strong performance.', source: 'Reuters', time: '6 hours ago', category: 'Automotive' }, { id: 4, title: 'Oil Prices Surge on Supply Concerns', summary: 'Crude oil futures rise amid geopolitical tensions in key producing regions.', source: 'Bloomberg', time: '8 hours ago', category: 'Energy' } ]; return (
{/* Header */}

Market News

{/* News Feed */}
{newsItems.map((item) => (
{item.category} {item.time}

{item.title}

{item.summary}

{item.source}
))}
{/* Bottom Navigation */}
); }; export default NewsScreen;
